<paragraph blockId="2.[159,801,738,889]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">branchial arch 1 + 7. Vomerine teeth absent. Preopercular canal absent. Dermosphenotic absent. Ventral process of posttemporal absent. Neural prezygapophyses long, about 25 % of neural spine length in fifth caudal vertebra. Epipleural ribs rod-like. Total vertebrae 29-30.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[159,802,930,1209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[159,288,930,954]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Coloration.</emphasis>
Unknown in live specimens, but faint dark marks weakly observable in preserved specimens. Flank of male with brown stripes and oblique brown bars on anterodorsal portion; female with irregular brown marks. Postorbital dark brown blotch and transverse preorbital bar through chin in both sexes. Dorsal fin with subbasal stripe, darker in female. No dark marks on anal fin. Caudal fin with brown bars on basal portion, darker in female; reddish brown marginal stripe around fin in male.
</paragraph>
